<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="5" MadCap:lastHeight="749" MadCap:lastWidth="839">
    <head>
        <link href="../../Stylesheets/styles.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="tip">
            <p class="tipInDiv" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #a5910a;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Tip: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">When you click on a cursor in a frame, you will see a blue line with circles representing the beginning and end point of the trajectory. However, this trajectory is based on the upper-left corner of the object, rather than the center of the object.</p>
            <p>The default look for a cursor is a translucent circle with an arrow cursor in it. So if you click and drag the blue circle representing the end of the trajectory, keep in mind that where you drop the circle is actually the upper-left of the object when it finishes.</p>
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicMovieEnhancementGuide" />
            <p>For example, the following cursor was created automatically after a movie was recorded. The cursor moves so that the arrow finishes on the button that has the A and red bar under it.</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/cursor_position_keyframes2.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicMovieEnhancementGuide" />
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicWhatsNewGuide" />
            <p>If you click the Play button at the bottom of the frame (or if you click and drag the scrubber), you can see the actual path of the trajectory.</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/cursor_position_keyframes3.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicWhatsNewGuide" />
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicMovieEnhancementGuide" />
            <p>Let's say you decide to adjust the trajectory so that it ends on the paint bucket button. When dragging the blue circle representing the end point, make sure you drop it to the upper-left of the paint bucket button, rather than on the button itself. Then test the results with the Play button or scrubber.</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/cursor_position_keyframes4.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" /> </p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>